	<td class="alt1">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Brainstorm'in...</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>We complain alot about a lack of creativity.. let's see what we can come up with as far as new idea's for the class .. gear/aa/spell/etc..<br />
<br />
I'll start off with a mix of idea's that I've either seen and liked.. or are my own..<br />
<br />
Focus Augments:  These would increase the minimum % from 1-5% ...another aug from 5-10%  and another aug from 10-15%.  Of course they would only work for one element..  and you'd have to upgrade them in order.. or even have to use additional aug slots .. either way though , you'd have to get all three in order.(If this isn't really possible to code, someone speak up .. )<br />
<br />
Stun Crowd Control :  Low damage, -100 to resists and max of 4 .. typical stun time frame is fine.. typical refresh..  This would be a mix of our bane, stun, and pillar series in my line of thinking.  (AA or spell)<br />
<br />
Indoor Mount :  Have always felt this would be so helpful.. <br />
<br />
Armor focus proc's :  When hit, could proc an effect similar to necro mind wrack.. thinking particularly of AE spell hits.. no, I don't want wizards trying to get hit for this proc !! lol<br />
<br />
LavaFlood :  provided it's not resisted, creatures will be swept down a path the wizard is facing.. for a set time period.. and it will occur at snare speed.. (In other words the creatures will start moving in that direction at snare speed, so yes, while in range they could smack someone).  I think a minor dmg of 300 per tick wouldn't be to bad, it's a lava flood after all.<br />
<br />
Flappy Scout:  Have always liked the idea of being flappy.. seeing thru his eyes etc..  <br />
<br />
Flappy Fire :   Wizard channels mana energy into his flappy.. where it will be stored.. up to a certain amount and can only be held by the flappy for so long, flappy simply can't handle the strain..  Once stored, the wizard has a certain amount of time to activate the release.. The flappy will then spray fire at the wizards target doing...X amount of damage..   I think this would be a different aa.. could have the flappy simply explode as well.. dmg should be substantial... Could have it for each element as well.<br />
<br />
Elemental rage:  Wizard can choose Magic / Ice/ Fire ... Ice, magic or fire burst flow from the caster mana free for a determined X amount of time doing X dmg..  at a single target...  <br />
<br />
Keep in mind these are pretty much off the top of my head.. there only meant to brainchild better versions of an idea or at least discuss things.. Let's see what we can come up with guys and let's avoid the debate for a while and just try to provide some inspiration...</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
