		<div>I suggested a solution for sustained damage <a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?t=27564" target="_blank">here, Innate ability for sustained damage</a><br />
<br />
Basic idea: when a wizard become lom or oom he/she can use an innate ability (with a very low token mana cost) to sustain 200dps while regenning mana for new bursts. <br />
<br />
It would mean wizards never have to hit 0dps when oom, (can even be used if correctly timed with manadrain). Other caster classes have pet dps when oom, wizards have none. If given to wizards as an innate ability (that scale with lvl) it can fix the sustained damage problem wizards face throughout the lvls (1-70).</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
