		<div>I love this kind of thread, so I'll repeat some of my favorite ideas.  <br />
<br />
<br />
1. The Mega Blast---really large nuke that takes really big chunk of mana..say a ratio of not higher than 2:1, but has a recourse that returns 90% of the mana used over 20 seconds.  The recourse does not stack with itself, so successive castings of the spell will net a horrible mana ratio unless you wait for the recourse to finish.  This would be similar to the usefullness of Ice Spear and it's siblings, with the option of really huge burst dps instead of efficiency.  I'm thinking a base damage of 5000 damage for 3000 mana, but only costs 300 mana if you want to wait for it, with a cast time of 3 seconds.  Ro's Unstable Draught anyone?<br />
<br />
2. A Xuzl Sword that actually works---and make sure this one actually flames too.<br />
<br />
3. increase our Damage Shield line to match the damage that chanter's DS can do, and make it actually stack with everything, including the bard DS songs and the druid/mage ds's.<br />
<br />
4. Ranged weapons (wands) that use Evocation as their weapon skill so that we can actually hit with them.  A line of AA's similar to ranger style archery aa's to go with it.  Itemized throughout the game from a newbie quest from the guy who takes your note and gives you a guild tunic, to endgame uber mob drops.  Ammo is Manacrystals, with specialty versions created for different damage types: magic, cold, fire, and Poison-- specialty versions crafted by Enchanters (magic), Wizards (cold), Mages (fire), and Necros (Poison).<br />
<br />
5. Return of the Manastone!---sorry, just a pet-peeve of mine from way back in the day.  Make the manastone into a FT 3 Mana preservation focus item and put it back in Guk.  Put Greater Manastones on the Guk LDON merchant, that are FT 5 items with a right click of C3 for 1500pts.  Add Lesser Manastone to LDON Guk merchant as a FT1 Item that right clicks Breeze for 15ish points.  Watch the lemming flood of casters marching into guk...  oh, and make the click effects of the manastones require the solidified mana from a chanter to use.  That way they can stop selling KEI in PoK, and start selling Vials of mana in the Bazaar....</div>
