</div>
				
				<div>
					
					
				</div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				I would hate to see anything taken care of through items, just because not everyone would have access to them. My GoD spells in particular come to mind on things I could use but will probably never see the light of day.
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
<br />
I agree completly, which is why when I suggest anything be fixed through items, I qualify that by saying it should be an entire line of items, not just 'an item'.<br />
<br />
For instance, one major wizard concern has always been sustained damage.  The easiest and most obvious answer to that is wizard usable weapons.  But...and this is a deal breaker, if we are going to address wizard sustained damage problems, we need to address it from level 1 up.  They can't just toss us a robe that drops in Veeshan's Peak or off Velkator and call us balanced.  Those items only helped the 1% of the wizards at the time that could get them.<br />
<br />
<br />
I can see a whole range of items that would help wizards.  Wands that cast a specific spell, but do so for 4 times the mana on a 1 second cast--this could be Force Shock or Rend, or Agnar's, depending on the level it's intended for.  <br />
<br />
Wands that are basically weapons that do mana free ranged damage and use evocation as it's attack skill---easily balanced for any level of play. Even a similar wand that is a weapon, that is super accurate but less damaging, but uses divination as it's attack skill, and includes a debuff of some kind along with it's damage.<br />
<br />
How about Spellbooks?  Let's just say that instead of just being a stat item, Velk's Spell book opened like a book when clicked, and had spells that could be memed into your spellbook inside that could only be found in that spellbook.  You would have to have the book equipped to cast the spell, but when you moved on, you could sell the spell book to an up and coming caster.  BOOM, some spells are now balanced similarly to weapon upgrades. It would also have the limitation of being a spell that was not available till you got your corpse, as you have to have the book to mem the spell.  The spells themselves would not be limited to a level to be memmed, only that you have the book to get the spell out of, and have the book equipped to cast the spell.<br />
<br />
This would not be limited to high levels either.  These elite spellbooks could be quested for in your guild, could be added to any of the stat spellbooks in the game from the one off Najena to the one off Velk.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2">
		<img class="inlineimg" src="images/statusicon/user_offline.gif" alt="Necridious is offline" border="0" />


		
		
		
		&nbsp;
	</td>
	<td class="alt1" align="right">
